ge Athan Billias traces the spread of American constitutionalism-from Europe, Latin America, and the Caribbean region, to Asia and Africa-beginning chronologically with the American Revolution and the fateful "shot heard round the world" and ending with the conclusion of the Cold War in 1989. The American model contributed significantly by spearheading the drive to greater democracy throughout the Western world, and Billias's landmark study tells a story that will change the way readers view the important role American constitutionalism played during this era.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aCivilization, ModernxAmerican influences. 0aConstitutional historyzUnited States. 0aConstitutional history. 0aConstitutional lawzUnited States. 0aConstitutional law. 0aWorld politicsy1900-1945. 0aWorld politicsy1945-1989. 0aWorld politicsyTo 1900. 4a1989. 4aAmerican. 4aBilliass. 4aWestern. 4achange. 4aconstitutionalism. 4aduring. 4aera. 4aglobal. 4ahistory. 4aimportant. 4alandmark. 4amajor. 4aplayed. 4apoint. 4areached. 4areaders. 4arole. 4astory. 4astudy. 4atells. 4athat. 4athis. 4aturning. 4aview. 4awill. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP Backlist 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814739013423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814739013.jpg  a978-3-11-070644-4  NYUP Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK